  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      PURPOSE: Autotransfusion devices may be employed in cardiac surgery to decrease allogenic
      blood requirements. Limitations of previous trials include the use of cell saver systems in
      selected high risk patients only or the lack of blood transfusion-sparing strategies. The aim
      of this prospective randomized study is to evaluate the efficacy of cell salvage CardioPAT
      routinely used in cardiac surgery.

      METHODS: The investigators will randomize 350 patients in two groups: group 1 receives a
      CardioPAT cell saver device (175 patients), group 2 doesn't receive any cell saver device.
      The incidence of allogenic blood transfusion and clinical outcome in both groups are
      evaluated.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
